{"reasoning":"The bug is in order_service.place_order: it reserves inventory and writes an audit entry before payment, but if payment fails it re-raises without undoing either side effect. This leaves inventory reserved and the audit log polluted after a declined payment. The fix is to perform compensating rollback in the exception path: release the reserved quantity and remove the audit entry for that order before re-raising. I also cleaned up reset() so it no longer assigns unrelated globals and instead resets notifications plus the imported inventory/payment modules, which avoids stale partial state in tests or repeated runs. No changes are required in inventory.py or payment.py because they already expose the necessary release/remove primitives.","files":{"code_snippets_v2/partial_rollback_c/inventory.py":""""Inventory management with reservation tracking."""

